Foods That Are Good for Your Liver","abstract":"These foods will keep this vital organ thriving.","url":"https://www.msn.com/en-ca/health/nutrition/7-foods-that-are-good-for-your-liver/ss-AA1aqZAy","locale":"en-us","isLocalContent":false,"galleryItemCount":0,"slides":[{"body":"<p>YOU MIGHT NOT express gratitude for your <a href=\\"https://www.menshealth.com/uk/health/a30116737/liver-drink-too-much/\\">liver</a> (or even think about it) much, but it\xE2\x80\x99s working around the clock for you.</p><p>It's a very impressive <a href=\\"https://www.menshealth.com/health/a39443190/organ-donor-crisis-solution/\\">organ</a>, says <a href=\\"https://profiles.mountsinai.org/meena-b-bansal\\">Meena B. Bansal, M.D</a>., professor of medicine, and director of translational research in liver diseases at the Icahn School of Medicine at Mount Sinai. It's the first line of defense for any <a href=\\"https://www.menshealth.com/health/a42621421/how-toxic-is-your-body/\\">toxin</a> that may try to make its way into our system.</p><p>The liver is incredibly resistant to injury, and seriously resilient. Did you know your liver <a href=\\"https://www.nih.gov/news-events/nih-research-matters/cells-maintain-repair-liver-identified#:~:text=A%20liver%20can%20regrow%20to,overdoses%2C%20and%20fatty%20liver%20disease.\\">can grow back</a> to a normal size even after up to 90 percent of it has been removed?</p><p>Still, it\xE2\x80\x99s important that you avoid things that hurt your liver such as excess <a href=\\"https://www.menshealth.com/nutrition/a27491762/healthiest-ways-to-drink-alcohol/\\">alcohol</a>, recreational <a href=\\"https://www.menshealth.com/health/a42270129/gas-station-dope-tianeptine/\\">drugs</a>, and some <a href=\\"https://www.menshealth.com/nutrition/a19539297/the-top-10-supplements-for-men/\\">dietary supplements</a>, said Bansal. \xE2\x80\x9CModeration is the key to everything.\\"</p><p>Ahead, a primer on all the liver\xE2\x80\x99s incredible functions and top foods to eat to support the star organ.</p><h4 class=\\"body-h4\\">What Does the Liver Do?</h4><p>You can consider the liver as the gatekeeper to everything we intake, Bansal says. When you eat food or take medications, all the blood flow from the stomach and intestines is first filtered through the liver which then detoxifies medications, metabolizes carbohydrates, lipids and clears bacterial products that may have escaped the gut.</p><p>\xE2\x80\x9CIn addition, it makes proteins like clotting factors and maintains healthy blood sugar levels,\xE2\x80\x9D she adds. \xE2\x80\x9CIt produces bile that is needed to help us digest and absorb fats in the small intestine.\xE2\x80\x9D</p><p>The liver is your body\xE2\x80\x99s \xE2\x80\x9Cmetabolic powerhouse,\xE2\x80\x9D says <a href=\\"https://crossfit26.com/\\">Kim Yawitz</a>, R.D., a gym owner in St. Louis, Mo. Everything you ingest passes through this gate. The good stuff, like food is broken down into energy and nutrients, then distributed throughout the body or stored away for later use. The bad stuff, like toxins, are filtered out of the blood to be excreted via urine or stool.</p><p>\xE2\x80\x9CThe liver is responsible for hundreds of life-sustaining functions, so it\xE2\x80\x99s really important to take good care of it,\xE2\x80\x9D Yawitz says.</p><p>What Makes a Food Good for the Liver?</p><p>There are several things that make foods liver-friendly.</p><p>Bansal says foods that are anti-inflammatory or have antioxidant properties are beneficial to the liver. Foods that are high in fiber and promote a healthy weight are also helpful to the liver.</p><p>\xE2\x80\x9CHighly processed foods that contain fructose corn-syrup are bad for the liver as they cause the liver cells to make unhealthy lipids (fat). As this fat accumulates, it can cause liver injury and inflammation,\xE2\x80\x9D she says. Basically, the less processed and unadulterated the food you eat, the better. \xE2\x80\x9CThink farm to table.\xE2\x80\x9D</p><p>As a rule of thumb, Bansal says that foods that you think of as good for your heart are also ones that are good for your liver. Just as the <a href=\\"https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/31334554/\\">Mediterranean Diet</a> is known to support cardiovascular health, so does it for your liver. There is no one food in this diet plan that is driving the <a href=\\"https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/30033779/\\">beneficial effects</a>, but rather it's the combination of its multiple components, says Bansal.</p><p>\xE2\x80\x9CConceptually an overall diet that is 50 percent fruits, vegetables, whole grains, lentils, legumes; 30 percent healthy fat (think avocados, extra-virgin olive oil); 20 percent lean protein from chicken and fish containing omega-3 fatty acids is considered the best combination,\xE2\x80\x9D she says.</p><p>While there\xE2\x80\x99s no single food that will magically improve liver health, foods high in fiber, healthy fats, and certain antioxidants support optimal liver function. Not surprising\xE2\x80\x94 alcohol and drugs can damage the liver, as can eating too much sugar, salt, and <a href=\\"https://www.frontiersin.org/articles/10.3389/fnut.2021.640557/full\\">saturated fat</a>.</p><p>Overall, healthy lifestyle choices are healthy liver choices. \xE2\x80\x9CThe <a href=\\"https://www.frontiersin.org/articles/10.3389/fnut.2021.640557/full\\">best ways to protect your liver</a> are to eat a well-balanced diet, exercise, and maintain a healthy body weight,\xE2\x80\x9D says Yawitz.</p>","image":{"width":2121,"height":1414,"quality":79,"url":"https://img-s-msn-com.akamaized.net/tenant/amp/entityid/AA1aroqk.img","attribution":"Klaus Vedfelt - Getty Images","title":"7 Foods That Are Good for Your Liver","caption":"<p>YOU MIGHT NOT express gratitude for your <a href=\\"https://www.menshealth.com/uk/health/a30116737/liver-drink-too-much/\\">liver</a> (or even think about it) much, but it\xE2\x80\x99s working around the clock for you.</p><p>It's a very impressive <a href=\\"https://www.menshealth.com/health/a39443190/organ-donor-crisis-solution/\\">organ</a>, says <a href=\\"https://profiles.mountsinai.org/meena-b-bansal\\">Meena B. Not surprising\xE2\x80\x94 alcohol and drugs can damage the liver, as can eating too much sugar, salt, and <a href=\\"https://www.frontiersin.org/articles/10.3389/fnut.2021.640557/full\\">saturated fat</a>.</p><p>Overall, healthy lifestyle choices are healthy liver choices. \xE2\x80\x9CThe <a href=\\"https://www.frontiersin.org/articles/10.3389/fnut.2021.640557/full\\">best ways to protect your liver</a> are to eat a well-balanced diet, exercise, and maintain a healthy body weight,\xE2\x80\x9D says Yawitz.</p>","source":"msn"}},{"title":"1) Coffee","body":"<p>Okay, we know it\xE2\x80\x99s technically a beverage, but we\xE2\x80\x99re putting this one first.</p><p>\\"The only food where there is clear <a href=\\"https://bmcpublichealth.biomedcentral.com/articles/10.1186/s12889-021-10991-7\\">evidence</a> for a <a href=\\"https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/abs/pii/S1542356521010570\\">beneficial</a> impact on your liver is coffee,\xE2\x80\x9D says Bansal. \xE2\x80\x9CCoffee consumption is associated with improvement in liver enzymes, especially in individuals with risk for liver disease.\\"</p><p>Those with pre-existing liver disease have shown improvements in incidence rates of fibrosis and cirrhosis (scarring of the liver), liver cancer, and overall mortality when given three or more cups of coffee per day, she says. Interestingly, scientists do not completely understand what exact components of coffee are conferring the benefit since there are numerous compounds in coffee, but it is thought to be the combination.</p><p>Ideally, you should drink black caffeinated coffee to avoid the excess calories that come from cream and sugar, Bansal says. It's worth noting that decaffeinated coffee does not confer the same benefit as regular coffee, but there is no clear evidence that caffeine is the driver of the benefits. Don't get any ideas, though\xE2\x80\x94caffeine supplements are not going to provide the same effect.</p><p>Not a coffee drinker? Black tea may prove helpful for liver health too, though it might not be to the same effect, Bansal says. \xE2\x80\x9CSo if you have a choice, drink coffee. If you cannot drink coffee then black tea may have some benefit albeit much smaller.\xE2\x80\x9D</p>","image":{"width":1200,"height":800,"quality":79,"url":"https://img-s-msn-com.akamaized.net/tenant/amp/entityid/AA1ar2g1.img","attribution":"d3sign - Getty Images","title":"1) Coffee","caption":"<p>Okay, we know it\xE2\x80\x99s technically a beverage, but we\xE2\x80\x99re putting this one first.</p><p>\\"The only food where there is clear <a href=\\"https://bmcpublichealth.biomedcentral.com/articles/10.1186/s12889-021-10991-7\\">evidence</a> for a <a href=\\"https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/abs/pii/S1542356521010570\\">beneficial</a> impact on your liver is coffee,\xE2\x80\x9D says Bansal. \xE2\x80\x9CCoffee consumption is associated with improvement in liver enzymes, especially in individuals with risk for liver disease.\\"</p><p>Those with pre-existing liver disease have shown improvements in incidence rates of fibrosis and cirrhosis (scarring of the liver), liver cancer, and overall mortality when given three or more cups of coffee per day, she says. It's the first line of defense for any <a href=\\"https://www.menshealth.com/health/a42621421/how-toxic-is-your-body/\\">toxin</a> that may try to make its way into our system.</p><p>The liver is incredibly resistant to injury, and seriously resilient. Did you know your liver <a href=\\"https://www.nih.gov/news-events/nih-research-matters/cells-maintain-repair-liver-identified#:~:text=A%20liver%20can%20regrow%20to,overdoses%2C%20and%20fatty%20liver%20disease.\\">can grow back</a> to a normal size even after up to 90 percent of it has been removed?</p><p>Still, it\xE2\x80\x99s important that you avoid things that hurt your liver such as excess <a href=\\"https://www.menshealth.com/nutrition/a27491762/healthiest-ways-to-drink-alcohol/\\">alcohol</a>, recreational <a href=\\"https://www.menshealth.com/health/a42270129/gas-station-dope-tianeptine/\\">drugs</a>, and some <a href=\\"https://www.menshealth.com/nutrition/a19539297/the-top-10-supplements-for-men/\\">dietary supplements</a>, said Bansal. \xE2\x80\x9CModeration is the key to everything.\\"</p><p>Ahead, a primer on all the liver\xE2\x80\x99s incredible functions and top foods to eat to support the star organ.</p><h4 class=\\"body-h4\\">What Does the Liver Do?</h4><p>You can consider the liver as the gatekeeper to everything we intake, Bansal says. When you eat food or take medications, all the blood flow from the stomach and intestines is first filtered through the liver which then detoxifies medications, metabolizes carbohydrates, lipids and clears bacterial products that may have escaped the gut.</p><p>\xE2\x80\x9CIn addition, it makes proteins like clotting factors and maintains healthy blood sugar levels,\xE2\x80\x9D she adds. \xE2\x80\x9CIt produces bile that is needed to help us digest and absorb fats in the small intestine.\xE2\x80\x9D</p><p>The liver is your body\xE2\x80\x99s \xE2\x80\x9Cmetabolic powerhouse,\xE2\x80\x9D says <a href=\\"https://crossfit26.com/\\">Kim Yawitz</a>, R.D., a gym owner in St. Louis, Mo. Everything you ingest passes through this gate. The good stuff, like food is broken down into energy and nutrients, then distributed throughout the body or stored away for later use. The bad stuff, like toxins, are filtered out of the blood to be excreted via urine or stool.</p><p>\xE2\x80\x9CThe liver is responsible for hundreds of life-sustaining functions, so it\xE2\x80\x99s really important to take good care of it,\xE2\x80\x9D Yawitz says.</p><p>What Makes a Food Good for the Liver?</p><p>There are several things that make foods liver-friendly.</p><p>Bansal says foods that are anti-inflammatory or have antioxidant properties are beneficial to the liver. Foods that are high in fiber and promote a healthy weight are also helpful to the liver.</p><p>\xE2\x80\x9CHighly processed foods that contain fructose corn-syrup are bad for the liver as they cause the liver cells to make unhealthy lipids (fat). As this fat accumulates, it can cause liver injury and inflammation,\xE2\x80\x9D she says. Basically, the less processed and unadulterated the food you eat, the better. \xE2\x80\x9CThink farm to table.\xE2\x80\x9D</p><p>As a rule of thumb, Bansal says that foods that you think of as good for your heart are also ones that are good for your liver. Just as the <a href=\\"https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/31334554/\\">Mediterranean Diet</a> is known to support cardiovascular health, so does it for your liver. There is no one food in this diet plan that is driving the <a href=\\"https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/30033779/\\">beneficial effects</a>, but rather it's the combination of its multiple components, says Bansal.</p><p>\xE2\x80\x9CConceptually an overall diet that is 50 percent fruits, vegetables, whole grains, lentils, legumes; 30 percent healthy fat (think avocados, extra-virgin olive oil); 20 percent lean protein from chicken and fish containing omega-3 fatty acids is considered the best combination,\xE2\x80\x9D she says.</p><p>While there\xE2\x80\x99s no single food that will magically improve liver health, foods high in fiber, healthy fats, and certain antioxidants support optimal liver function. Not surprising\xE2\x80\x94 alcohol and drugs can damage the liver, as can eating too much sugar, salt, and <a href=\\"https://www.frontiersin.org/articles/10.3389/fnut.2021.640557/full\\">saturated fat</a>.</p><p>Overall, healthy lifestyle choices are healthy liver choices. \xE2\x80\x9CThe <a href=\\"https://www.frontiersin.org/articles/10.3389/fnut.2021.640557/full\\">best ways to protect your liver</a> are to eat a well-balanced diet, exercise, and maintain a healthy body weight,\xE2\x80\x9D says Yawitz.</p>","source":"msn","colorSamples":[{"isDarkMode":true,"hexColor":"#303d42","isGreyScale":false},{"isDarkMode":false,"hexColor":"#efe7dd","isGreyScale":false}]}],"colorSamples":[{"isDarkMode":true,"hexColor":"#303d42","secHexColor":"#2f3e3c","gradientAngle":"135deg","isGreyScale":false},{"isDarkMode":false,"hexColor":"#efe7dd","secHexColor":"#efe6e5","gradientAngle":"135deg","isGreyScale":false}],"provider":{"id":"BBJ4kTa","name":"Men's we were to define the word\xE2\x80\x9C<a href=\\"https://www.delish.com/best-cocktail-recipes/\\">cocktail</a>\xE2\x80\x9D for you here, you\xE2\x80\x99d think we were crazy. <em>Everyone</em> knows what a cocktail is, right? Well, not in 1806 they didn\xE2\x80\x99t. May 13, 1806 was one of the very first times the word cocktail was first defined in print, in response to a reader inquiry to the New York federalist newspaper <em>The Balance and Columbian Repository</em>. They wrote that a \xE2\x80\x9Ccock-tail\xE2\x80\xA6is a stimulating liquor, composed of <a href=\\"https://www.delish.com/kitchen-tools/a43510984/our-expert-guide-to-stocking-a-portable-bar/\\">spirits</a> of any kind, sugar, water, and <a href=\\"https://www.delish.com/food/a42397151/bitters-soda-dry-january/\\">bitters</a>.\xE2\x80\x9D A bit of a far cry from the cocktails we know and love today, sure, but we had to start somewhere! To commemorate the occasion, World Cocktail Day is now celebrated on May 13 every year. Join us in celebration by being your own bartender and enjoying your mixology with a little bit of history this World Cocktail Day.</p><p>These cocktails all feature ingredients, liquors, and recipes from around the globe (and some from closer to home). Big <a href=\\"https://www.delish.com/entertaining/g31903538/best-tequila-brands/\\">tequila</a> fan? We bet you\xE2\x80\x99ve had a Mexican <a href=\\"https://www.delish.com/cooking/recipe-ideas/a20139300/best-classic-margarita-recipe/\\">margarita</a> before, but what about their lesser-known cocktail, the <a href=\\"https://www.delish.com/cooking/recipe-ideas/a43758194/paloma-cocktail-recipe/\\">Paloma</a>? Love the spiced-sweet flavor of <a href=\\"https://www.delish.com/entertaining/g32009640/best-rum-brands/\\">rum</a>? Head to the tropics and try a <a href=\\"https://www.delish.com/cooking/recipe-ideas/a34099414/painkiller-cocktail-recipe/\\">Painkiller</a>, a <a href=\\"https://www.delish.com/cooking/recipe-ideas/a38885892/dark-and-stormy-recipe/\\">Dark & Stormy</a>, or a <a href=\\"https://www.delish.com/cooking/recipe-ideas/a28903015/rum-and-coke-recipe/\\">Cuba Libre</a>. Love an <a href=\\"https://www.delish.com/food/a41652646/american-amaro-moment/\\">amaro</a>? Italy\xE2\x80\x99s got you\xE2\x80\x94their <a href=\\"https://www.delish.com/cooking/recipe-ideas/recipes/a9535/americano-recipe/\\">Americano</a>, <a href=\\"https://www.delish.com/cooking/recipe-ideas/a38688424/negroni-recipe/\\">Negroni</a>, or <a href=\\"https://www.delish.com/cooking/recipe-ideas/a36756262/aperol-spritz-recipe/\\">Aperol Spritz</a> is the perfect combo of bittersweet and refreshing.</p><p>Looking to fully branch out, no matter where your cocktails originated? Well, not in 1806 they didn\xE2\x80\x99t. May 13, 1806 was one of the very first times the word cocktail was first defined in print, in response to a reader inquiry to the New York federalist newspaper <em>The Balance and Columbian Repository</em>. They wrote that a \xE2\x80\x9Ccock-tail\xE2\x80\xA6is a stimulating liquor, composed of <a href=\\"https://www.delish.com/kitchen-tools/a43510984/our-expert-guide-to-stocking-a-portable-bar/\\">spirits</a> of any kind, sugar, water, and <a href=\\"https://www.delish.com/food/a42397151/bitters-soda-dry-january/\\">bitters</a>.\xE2\x80\x9D A bit of a far cry from the cocktails we know and love today, sure, but we had to start somewhere! Foods That Are Good for Your Liver","abstract":"These foods will keep this vital organ thriving.","url":"https://www.msn.com/en-ca/health/nutrition/7-foods-that-are-good-for-your-liver/ss-AA1aqZAy","locale":"en-us","isLocalContent":false,"galleryItemCount":0,"slides":[{"body":"<p>YOU MIGHT NOT express gratitude for your <a href=\\"https://www.menshealth.com/uk/health/a30116737/liver-drink-too-much/\\">liver</a> (or even think about it) much, but it\xE2\x80\x99s working around the clock for you.</p><p>It's a very impressive <a href=\\"https://www.menshealth.com/health/a39443190/organ-donor-crisis-solution/\\">organ</a>, says <a href=\\"https://profiles.mountsinai.org/meena-b-bansal\\">Meena B. Bansal, M.D</a>., professor of medicine, and director of translational research in liver diseases at the Icahn School of Medicine at Mount Sinai. It's the first line of defense for any <a href=\\"https://www.menshealth.com/health/a42621421/how-toxic-is-your-body/\\">toxin</a> that may try to make its way into our system.</p><p>The liver is incredibly resistant to injury, and seriously resilient. Did you know your liver <a href=\\"https://www.nih.gov/news-events/nih-research-matters/cells-maintain-repair-liver-identified#:~:text=A%20liver%20can%20regrow%20to,overdoses%2C%20and%20fatty%20liver%20disease.\\">can grow back</a> to a normal size even after up to 90 percent of it has been removed?</p><p>Still, it\xE2\x80\x99s important that you avoid things that hurt your liver such as excess <a href=\\"https://www.menshealth.com/nutrition/a27491762/healthiest-ways-to-drink-alcohol/\\">alcohol</a>, recreational <a href=\\"https://www.menshealth.com/health/a42270129/gas-station-dope-tianeptine/\\">drugs</a>, and some <a href=\\"https://www.menshealth.com/nutrition/a19539297/the-top-10-supplements-for-men/\\">dietary supplements</a>, said Bansal. \xE2\x80\x9CModeration is the key to everything.\\"</p><p>Ahead, a primer on all the liver\xE2\x80\x99s incredible functions and top foods to eat to support the star organ.</p><h4 class=\\"body-h4\\">What Does the Liver Do?</h4><p>You can consider the liver as the gatekeeper to everything we intake, Bansal says. When you eat food or take medications, all the blood flow from the stomach and intestines is first filtered through the liver which then detoxifies medications, metabolizes carbohydrates, lipids and clears bacterial products that may have escaped the gut.</p><p>\xE2\x80\x9CIn addition, it makes proteins like clotting factors and maintains healthy blood sugar levels,\xE2\x80\x9D she adds. \xE2\x80\x9CIt produces bile that is needed to help us digest and absorb fats in the small intestine.\xE2\x80\x9D</p><p>The liver is your body\xE2\x80\x99s \xE2\x80\x9Cmetabolic powerhouse,\xE2\x80\x9D says <a href=\\"https://crossfit26.com/\\">Kim Yawitz</a>, R.D., a gym owner in St. Louis, Mo. Everything you ingest passes through this gate. The good stuff, like food is broken down into energy and nutrients, then distributed throughout the body or stored away for later use. The bad stuff, like toxins, are filtered out of the blood to be excreted via urine or stool.</p><p>\xE2\x80\x9CThe liver is responsible for hundreds of life-sustaining functions, so it\xE2\x80\x99s really important to take good care of it,\xE2\x80\x9D Yawitz says.</p><p>What Makes a Food Good for the Liver?</p><p>There are several things that make foods liver-friendly.</p><p>Bansal says foods that are anti-inflammatory or have antioxidant properties are beneficial to the liver. Foods that are high in fiber and promote a healthy weight are also helpful to the liver.</p><p>\xE2\x80\x9CHighly processed foods that contain fructose corn-syrup are bad for the liver as they cause the liver cells to make unhealthy lipids (fat). As this fat accumulates, it can cause liver injury and inflammation,\xE2\x80\x9D she says. Basically, the less processed and unadulterated the food you eat, the better. \xE2\x80\x9CThink farm to table.\xE2\x80\x9D</p><p>As a rule of thumb, Bansal says that foods that you think of as good for your heart are also ones that are good for your liver. Just as the <a href=\\"https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/31334554/\\">Mediterranean Diet</a> is known to support cardiovascular health, so does it for your liver. There is no one food in this diet plan that is driving the <a href=\\"https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/30033779/\\">beneficial effects</a>, but rather it's the combination of its multiple components, says Bansal.</p><p>\xE2\x80\x9CConceptually an overall diet that is 50 percent fruits, vegetables, whole grains, lentils, legumes; 30 percent healthy fat (think avocados, extra-virgin olive oil); 20 percent lean protein from chicken and fish containing omega-3 fatty acids is considered the best combination,\xE2\x80\x9D she says.</p><p>While there\xE2\x80\x99s no single food that will magically improve liver health, foods high in fiber, healthy fats, and certain antioxidants support optimal liver function. Not surprising\xE2\x80\x94 alcohol and drugs can damage the liver, as can eating too much sugar, salt, and <a href=\\"https://www.frontiersin.org/articles/10.3389/fnut.2021.640557/full\\">saturated fat</a>.</p><p>Overall, healthy lifestyle choices are healthy liver choices. \xE2\x80\x9CThe <a href=\\"https://www.frontiersin.org/articles/10.3389/fnut.2021.640557/full\\">best ways to protect your liver</a> are to eat a well-balanced diet, exercise, and maintain a healthy body weight,\xE2\x80\x9D says Yawitz.</p>","image":{"width":2121,"height":1414,"quality":79,"url":"https://img-s-msn-com.akamaized.net/tenant/amp/entityid/AA1aroqk.img","attribution":"Klaus Vedfelt - Getty Images","title":"7 Foods That Are Good for Your Liver","caption":"<p>YOU MIGHT NOT express gratitude for your <a href=\\"https://www.menshealth.com/uk/health/a30116737/liver-drink-too-much/\\">liver</a> (or even think about it) much, but it\xE2\x80\x99s working around the clock for you.</p><p>It's a very impressive <a href=\\"https://www.menshealth.com/health/a39443190/organ-donor-crisis-solution/\\">organ</a>, says <a href=\\"https://profiles.mountsinai.org/meena-b-bansal\\">Meena B. Bansal, M.D</a>., professor of medicine, and director of translational research in liver diseases at the Icahn School of Medicine at Mount Sinai. It's the first line of defense for any <a href=\\"https://www.menshealth.com/health/a42621421/how-toxic-is-your-body/\\">toxin</a> that may try to make its way into our system.</p><p>The liver is incredibly resistant to injury, and seriously resilient. Did you know your liver <a href=\\"https://www.nih.gov/news-events/nih-research-matters/cells-maintain-repair-liver-identified#:~:text=A%20liver%20can%20regrow%20to,overdoses%2C%20and%20fatty%20liver%20disease.\\">can grow back</a> to a normal size even after up to 90 percent of it has been removed?</p><p>Still, it\xE2\x80\x99s important that you avoid things that hurt your liver such as excess <a href=\\"https://www.menshealth.com/nutrition/a27491762/healthiest-ways-to-drink-alcohol/\\">alcohol</a>, recreational <a href=\\"https://www.menshealth.com/health/a42270129/gas-station-dope-tianeptine/\\">drugs</a>, and some <a href=\\"https://www.menshealth.com/nutrition/a19539297/the-top-10-supplements-for-men/\\">dietary supplements</a>, said Bansal. \xE2\x80\x9CModeration is the key to everything.\\"</p><p>Ahead, a primer on all the liver\xE2\x80\x99s incredible functions and top foods to eat to support the star organ.</p><h4 class=\\"body-h4\\">What Does the Liver Do?</h4><p>You can consider the liver as the gatekeeper to everything we intake, Bansal says. Everything you ingest passes through this gate. The good stuff, like food is broken down into energy and nutrients, then distributed throughout the body or stored away for later use. The bad stuff, like toxins, are filtered out of the blood to be excreted via urine or stool.</p><p>\xE2\x80\x9CThe liver is responsible for hundreds of life-sustaining functions, so it\xE2\x80\x99s really important to take good care of it,\xE2\x80\x9D Yawitz says.</p><p>What Makes a Food Good for the Liver?</p><p>There are several things that make foods liver-friendly.</p><p>Bansal says foods that are anti-inflammatory or have antioxidant properties are beneficial to the liver. Foods that are high in fiber and promote a healthy weight are also helpful to the liver.</p><p>\xE2\x80\x9CHighly processed foods that contain fructose corn-syrup are bad for the liver as they cause the liver cells to make unhealthy lipids (fat). As this fat accumulates, it can cause liver injury and inflammation,\xE2\x80\x9D she says. Basically, the less processed and unadulterated the food you eat, the better. \xE2\x80\x9CThink farm to table.\xE2\x80\x9D</p><p>As a rule of thumb, Bansal says that foods that you think of as good for your heart are also ones that are good for your liver. Just as the <a href=\\"https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/31334554/\\">Mediterranean Diet</a> is known to support cardiovascular health, so does it for your liver. There is no one food in this diet plan that is driving the <a href=\\"https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/30033779/\\">beneficial effects</a>, but rather it's the combination of its multiple components, says Bansal.</p><p>\xE2\x80\x9CConceptually an overall diet that is 50 percent fruits, vegetables, whole grains, lentils, legumes; 30 percent healthy fat (think avocados, extra-virgin olive oil); 20 percent lean protein from chicken and fish containing omega-3 fatty acids is considered the best combination,\xE2\x80\x9D she says.</p><p>While there\xE2\x80\x99s no single food that will magically improve liver health, foods high in fiber, healthy fats, and certain antioxidants support optimal liver function. Not surprising\xE2\x80\x94 alcohol and drugs can damage the liver, as can eating too much sugar, salt, and <a href=\\"https://www.frontiersin.org/articles/10.3389/fnut.2021.640557/full\\">saturated fat</a>.</p><p>Overall, healthy lifestyle choices are healthy liver choices. \xE2\x80\x9CThe <a href=\\"https://www.frontiersin.org/articles/10.3389/fnut.2021.640557/full\\">best ways to protect your liver</a> are to eat a well-balanced diet, exercise, and maintain a healthy body weight,\xE2\x80\x9D says Yawitz.</p>","source":"msn"}},{"title":"1) Coffee","body":"<p>Okay, we know it\xE2\x80\x99s technically a beverage, but we\xE2\x80\x99re putting this one first.</p><p>\\"The only food where there is clear <a href=\\"https://bmcpublichealth.biomedcentral.com/articles/10.1186/s12889-021-10991-7\\">evidence</a> for a <a href=\\"https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/abs/pii/S1542356521010570\\">beneficial</a> impact on your liver is coffee,\xE2\x80\x9D says Bansal. \xE2\x80\x9CCoffee consumption is associated with improvement in liver enzymes, especially in individuals with risk for liver disease.\\"</p><p>Those with pre-existing liver disease have shown improvements in incidence rates of fibrosis and cirrhosis (scarring of the liver), liver cancer, and overall mortality when given three or more cups of coffee per day, she says. Interestingly, scientists do not completely understand what exact components of coffee are conferring the benefit since there are numerous compounds in coffee, but it is thought to be the combination.</p><p>Ideally, you should drink black caffeinated coffee to avoid the excess calories that come from cream and sugar, Bansal says. It's worth noting that decaffeinated coffee does not confer the same benefit as regular coffee, but there is no clear evidence that caffeine is the driver of the benefits. Don't get any ideas, though\xE2\x80\x94caffeine supplements are not going to provide the same effect.</p><p>Not a coffee drinker? Black tea may prove helpful for liver health too, though it might not be to the same effect, Bansal says. \xE2\x80\x9CSo if you have a choice, drink coffee. If you cannot drink coffee then black tea may have some benefit albeit much smaller.\xE2\x80\x9D</p>","image":{"width":1200,"height":800,"quality":79,"url":"https://img-s-msn-com.akamaized.net/tenant/amp/entityid/AA1ar2g1.img","attribution":"d3sign - Getty Images","title":"1) Coffee","caption":"<p>Okay, we know it\xE2\x80\x99s technically a beverage, but we\xE2\x80\x99re putting this one first.</p><p>\\"The only food where there is clear <a href=\\"https://bmcpublichealth.biomedcentral.com/articles/10.1186/s12889-021-10991-7\\">evidence</a> for a <a href=\\"https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/abs/pii/S1542356521010570\\">beneficial</a> impact on your liver is coffee,\xE2\x80\x9D says Bansal. \xE2\x80\x9CCoffee consumption is associated with improvement in liver enzymes, especially in individuals with risk for liver disease.\\"</p><p>Those with pre-existing liver disease have shown improvements in incidence rates of fibrosis and cirrhosis (scarring of the liver), liver cancer, and overall mortality when given three or more cups of coffee per day, she says. Interestingly, scientists do not completely understand what exact components of coffee are conferring the benefit since there are numerous compounds in coffee, but it is thought to be the combination.</p><p>Ideally, you should drink black caffeinated coffee to avoid the excess calories that come from cream and sugar, Bansal says. It's worth noting that decaffeinated coffee does not confer the same benefit as regular coffee, but there is no clear evidence that caffeine is the driver of the benefits. Don't get any ideas, though\xE2\x80\x94caffeine supplements are not going to provide the same effect.</p><p>Not a coffee drinker? Black tea may prove helpful for liver health too, though it might not be to the same effect, Bansal says. \xE2\x80\x9CSo if you have a choice, drink coffee. If you cannot drink coffee then black tea may have some benefit albeit much smaller.\xE2\x80\x9D</p>","source":"msn"}},{"title":"2) Nuts","body":"<p>Here\xE2\x80\x99s another one that you may associate with heart health, but nuts don\xE2\x80\x99t just benefit your ticker. Nuts contain healthy fats and antioxidants, and they have been <a href=\\"https://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1111/liv.14164\\">associated</a> with a lower prevalence of fatty liver disease in men.</p>","source":"msn"}}],"publishedDateTime":"2023-05-23T20:08:13Z","isFeatured":false,"images":[{"width":2121,"height":1414,"url":"https://th.bing.com/th?id=ORMS.40a682b49fd6f59044a6d6aad509829a&pid=Wdp","title":"7 Foods That Are Good for Your Liver","caption":"<p>YOU MIGHT NOT express gratitude for your <a href=\\"https://www.menshealth.com/uk/health/a30116737/liver-drink-too-much/\\">liver</a> (or even think about it) much, but it\xE2\x80\x99s working around the clock for you.</p><p>It's a very impressive <a href=\\"https://www.menshealth.com/health/a39443190/organ-donor-crisis-solution/\\">organ</a>, says <a href=\\"https://profiles.mountsinai.org/meena-b-bansal\\">Meena B. Bansal, M.D</a>., professor of medicine, and director of translational research in liver diseases at the Icahn School of Medicine at Mount Sinai. It's the first line of defense for any <a href=\\"https://www.menshealth.com/health/a42621421/how-toxic-is-your-body/\\">toxin</a> that may try to make its way into our system.</p><p>The liver is incredibly resistant to injury, and seriously resilient. Did you know your liver <a href=\\"https://www.nih.gov/news-events/nih-research-matters/cells-maintain-repair-liver-identified#:~:text=A%20liver%20can%20regrow%20to,overdoses%2C%20and%20fatty%20liver%20disease.\\">can grow back</a> to a normal size even after up to 90 percent of it has been removed?</p><p>Still, it\xE2\x80\x99s important that you avoid things that hurt your liver such as excess <a href=\\"https://www.menshealth.com/nutrition/a27491762/healthiest-ways-to-drink-alcohol/\\">alcohol</a>, recreational <a href=\\"https://www.menshealth.com/health/a42270129/gas-station-dope-tianeptine/\\">drugs</a>, and some <a href=\\"https://www.menshealth.com/nutrition/a19539297/the-top-10-supplements-for-men/\\">dietary supplements</a>, said Bansal. \xE2\x80\x9CModeration is the key to everything.\\"</p><p>Ahead, a primer on all the liver\xE2\x80\x99s incredible functions and top foods to eat to support the star organ.</p><h4 class=\\"body-h4\\">What Does the Liver Do?</h4><p>You can consider the liver as the gatekeeper to everything we intake, Bansal says. When you eat food or take medications, all the blood flow from the stomach and intestines is first filtered through the liver which then detoxifies medications, metabolizes carbohydrates, lipids and clears bacterial products that may have escaped the gut.</p><p>\xE2\x80\x9CIn addition, it makes proteins like clotting factors and maintains healthy blood sugar levels,\xE2\x80\x9D she adds. \xE2\x80\x9CIt produces bile that is needed to help us digest and absorb fats in the small intestine.\xE2\x80\x9D</p><p>The liver is your body\xE2\x80\x99s \xE2\x80\x9Cmetabolic powerhouse,\xE2\x80\x9D says <a href=\\"https://crossfit26.com/\\">Kim Yawitz</a>, R.D., a gym owner in St. Louis, Mo. Everything you ingest passes through this gate. The good stuff, like food is broken down into energy and nutrients, then distributed throughout the body or stored away for later use. The bad stuff, like toxins, are filtered out of the blood to be excreted via urine or stool.</p><p>\xE2\x80\x9CThe liver is responsible for hundreds of life-sustaining functions, so it\xE2\x80\x99s really important to take good care of it,\xE2\x80\x9D Yawitz says.</p><p>What Makes a Food Good for the Liver?</p><p>There are several things that make foods liver-friendly.</p><p>Bansal says foods that are anti-inflammatory or have antioxidant properties are beneficial to the liver. Foods that are high in fiber and promote a healthy weight are also helpful to the liver.</p><p>\xE2\x80\x9CHighly processed foods that contain fructose corn-syrup are bad for the liver as they cause the liver cells to make unhealthy lipids (fat). As this fat accumulates, it can cause liver injury and inflammation,\xE2\x80\x9D she says. Basically, the less processed and unadulterated the food you eat, the better. \xE2\x80\x9CThink farm to table.\xE2\x80\x9D</p><p>As a rule of thumb, Bansal says that foods that you think of as good for your heart are also ones that are good for your liver. Just as the <a href=\\"https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/31334554/\\">Mediterranean Diet</a> is known to support cardiovascular health, so does it for your liver. There is no one food in this diet plan that is driving the <a href=\\"https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/30033779/\\">beneficial effects</a>, but rather it's the combination of its multiple components, says Bansal.</p><p>\xE2\x80\x9CConceptually an overall diet that is 50 percent fruits, vegetables, whole grains, lentils, legumes; 30 percent healthy fat (think avocados, extra-virgin olive oil); 20 percent lean protein from chicken and fish containing omega-3 fatty acids is considered the best combination,\xE2\x80\x9D she says.</p><p>While there\xE2\x80\x99s no single food that will magically improve liver health, foods high in fiber, healthy fats, and certain antioxidants support optimal liver function. Not surprising\xE2\x80\x94 alcohol and drugs can damage the liver, as can eating too much sugar, salt, and <a href=\\"https://www.frontiersin.org/articles/10.3389/fnut.2021.640557/full\\">saturated fat</a>.</p><p>Overall, healthy lifestyle choices are healthy liver choices. \xE2\x80\x9CThe <a href=\\"https://www.frontiersin.org/articles/10.3389/fnut.2021.640557/full\\">best ways to protect your Easy Black Bean Recipes for a Quick and Easy Dinner","abstract":"Here are a few dozen reasons to keep these dinner staples in stock.","url":"https://www.msn.com/en-ca/foodanddrink/recipes/29-easy-black-bean-recipes-for-a-quick-and-easy-dinner/ss-AA16Z0Eg","locale":"en-us","isLocalContent":false,"galleryItemCount":0,"slides":[{"body":"<p>If you're looking to add more versatile, easy-to-store, nutritious weeknight staple ingredients to your grocery list, then one of the best places you can turn is to the canned bean aisle of your local grocery store. Canned beans have it all: They're nutritious\xE2\x80\x94high in fiber as well as protein\xE2\x80\x94and they are relatively inexpensive and easy to store. They're also fast to cook with, and you can make them into dozens of different meals. While there are plenty of <a href=\\"https://www.countryliving.com/food-drinks/g30705886/types-of-beans/\\">types of beans</a> to choose from, we're particularly partial to canned black beans, partly because they're just so useful. </p><p>No can opener? No problem! You can always practice these techniques on <a href=\\"https://www.countryliving.com/food-drinks/a27338275/how-to-open-can-without-can-opener/\\">how to open a can without a can opener</a>, if you're in a pinch. (Though you might want to pick one up for the long term. <a href=\\"https://www.amazon.com/ZYLISS-Lock-Opener-Lifter-Magnet/dp/B000HK03HI/?tag=syndication-20&ascsubtag=%5Bartid%7C2141.g.42690392%5Bsrc%7Cmsn-us\\">Here's a good one</a> that's not expensive.)</p><p>You can use black beans to make all kinds of dishes, from cowboy caviar to salads and burritos to chili. They make a healthy addition to a loaded plate of nachos, and you can even blend them into brownies to add a little sneaky nutrition to an after-school snack or a post-dinner treat.
